Want your dock to resemble the look and feel of macOS? Follow these simple steps to set up a Mac-style dock on your GNOME desktop.

Steps
Visit the GNOME Extensions website: Dash to Dock Extension.
Click "Install" to add the Dash to Dock extension to your system.
This extension customizes your dock, allowing you to position it like a macOS dock and personalize its behavior and appearance.

Additional Configuration (Optional)
After installation, open the GNOME Extensions settings to tweak the dockâ€™s look, position, and animation styles.
